# Event Data Format (JSONC)

- Keep files human-readable and comment-rich for community PRs.
- Use JSONC (`.jsonc`) so inline comments can explain intent.
- Store one event per file under `data/events/`.
- Keep schema as single source of truth in `schemas/event.schema.ts`.
- Derive TypeScript types from JSON Schema instead of duplicating interfaces.

# Required Top-Level Fields

- `name`: display name, stable across editions.
- `slug`: URL-safe stable identifier.
- `location`: `{ city, country, venue }`.
- `links`: `{ website, fetlife, mailingList, contactEmail }`.
- `status`: one of `scheduled`, `on_sale`, `sold_out`, `waiting_list`, `tba`.
- `lastUpdated`: ISO date (`YYYY-MM-DD`) for staleness reminders.
- `historicalEditions`: array of known past editions.
- `nextEdition`: upcoming edition facts from sources; estimates are derived at runtime.

# Edition Structures

- `historicalEditions[]` item:
  - `startDate` / `endDate` (ISO date)
  - `announcementDate` (nullable)
  - `ticketSaleDate` (nullable)
  - `soldOutDate` (nullable)
  - `internalSourceNotes` (maintainer-facing raw provenance: URLs, FetLife event IDs, ambiguity notes)
  - `externalSourceNotes` (clean human-readable summary shown on the website)
- `nextEdition`:
  - `startDate` / `endDate` (nullable when unknown)
  - `announcementDate` (nullable)
  - `ticketSaleDate` (nullable)
  - `ticketUrl` (nullable)
  - `status` (same enum as top-level)

# Estimation Rule

- Never render past-only listings in the app.
- If no confirmed future date exists, estimates are calculated on the fly.
- Base estimates on historical cadence and lead-time medians from prior editions.

# Example Template

```jsonc
{
  // Stable event identity
  "name": "Prague Shibari Festival",
  "slug": "prague-shibari-festival",

  "location": {
    "city": "Prague",
    "country": "Czechia",
    "venue": "TBA after booking"
  },

  "links": {
    "website": "https://www.pragueshibari.com/",
    "fetlife": "https://fetlife.com/users/example",
    "mailingList": null,
    "contactEmail": null
  },

  "status": "scheduled",
  "lastUpdated": "2026-03-29",

  "historicalEditions": [],

  "nextEdition": {
    "startDate": "2026-09-11",
    "endDate": "2026-09-13",
    "announcementDate": null,
    "ticketSaleDate": null,
    "ticketUrl": "https://www.pragueshibari.com/",
    "status": "sold_out"
  }
}
```
